;arquebus, modified
;
INUMBER 696
NAME 868
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 10
ARTICLE SOME
PLURAL
CONTAINER IN
HIDDEN
*DESCRIPTION_START 
Mounted along the two walls of the deck are a dozen heavy arquebus.
The design has been heavily modified to allow various sizes and shapes
of missiles to be launched from them.
*DESCRIPTION_END 
IFPREVERB PULL -1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR ITEMBIT0 ! 1
    IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
      IFVAR ITEMVAL1 ! 1
        ECHO PLAYER You pull back the barrel, and drop in a heavy firepot.
        ECHO PLAYER [Round: 5 sec]
        EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
        ECHO OTHERS %n loads an arquebus.
        EQUAL ITEMBIT0 1
        AFFECT 1511
        EQUAL ITEMVAL5 EXITO
        EQUAL ITEMVAL1 1
       ELSE
        ECHO PLAYER Someone is using this arquebus.
     ELSE  
       STRCVT 0 ROUNDTIME
      ECHO PLAYER [Wait %0 seconds...]
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER The arquebus is already loaded.
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH -1
  CLEARVERB
  IFVAR ITEMBIT0 = 1
    IFVAR ROUNDTIME = 0
      ECHO PLAYER You jam the trigger of the arquebus forward, and the firepot shoots through the tube with an audible ZING! 
      ECHO OTHERS %n launches a firepot with the arquebus.
      EQUAL ITEMVAL1 0
      EQUAL ITEMBIT0 0
      AFFECT ITEMVAL5
      IFVAR PLRSINROOM ! 0
        DAMAGEALL BURN 40 A firepot falls from above and explodes at your feet!
      ENDIF
      ELSE
        STRCVT 0 ROUNDTIME
        ECHO PLAYER [Wait %0 seconds...]
    ELSE
      ECHO PLAYER The arquebus is not loaded.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
INUMBER 1265
NAME 1472
WEIGHT 1000
VOLUME 500
CONTAINER IN
INTERIOR 500
SUBSTANCE INSUBSTANTIAL
IFTOUCH -1
  IFVAR FLYING ! 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You can't reach that from here.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO -1
  IFVAR FLYING ! 1
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You can't reach the ship from here.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLYING = 1
  IFVAR ORG = 20
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER The armed guard stands aside and lets you pass.
    ECHO OTHERS %n boards the ship.
    MOVEGROUP 1503
   ENDIF
   IFVAR ORG ! 20
     CLEARVERB
      RANDOM DUMMY1 1 30 0
      EQUAL FLAG1 SKILL10
      DIV FLAG1 5
      ADD FLAG1 DUMMY1
      STRCVT 1 FLAG1
      GMMSG %N'S CHANCE TO BOARD THE SHIP IS %1.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR FLAG1 < 28
        DAMAGEPLR SLASH 10  You try to board the ship, but are blocked by an armed warrior.
        ECHO OTHERS %n tries to board the ship, but is turned back by an armed warrior.
     ENDIF
     IFVAR FLAG1 > 27
        ECHO OTHERS %n clambers over the wall of the ship.
        MOVE 1503
        AFFECT 1503
        ECHO ALL %n clambers over the wall onto the ship.%cAn armed guard raises an alarm.%cAn armed guard yells, "%n has boarded the ship!"
        AFFECT 1510
        ECHO ALL You hear an armed guard yell, "%n has just boarded the ship!"
        AFFECT 1511
        ECHO ALL You hear an armed guard yell, "%n has just boarded the ship!"
      ENDIF
    endif
;
*DESCRIPTION_START
Nearly 150 feet long, and 30 feet high, Thunderchild hovers in place
before you. Thinly hammered steel plates cover the entire outer hull,
adding a protective layer of armoring. The proud figure of Folknar,
Ancestor of War, cuts through the air ahead of the ship, and its sails
billow as if it were impatient to be on its way.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
