NUMBER 674
NAME Healers
INDOOR_FLOOR
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
You enter a small room, other then a desk and a blood stained mat that covers
the floor there is little here. Tending to those who need it you see Kridash,
a large, powerful drakin with scales that are jagged from age and old wounds.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 72 VAL2=1513 UNLOCKED
ITEM 1 1112

IFENTRY 
  ECHO PLAYER Kridash nods to you and continues to do his work.
  ECHO OTHERS Kridash nods to %N and continues to do his work.
ENDIF

IFPREVERB READ 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER The following spells are available by request.%c
  ECHO PLAYER   	Body Restoration III
  ECHO PLAYER	        Cure Poison
  ECHO PLAYER	        Cure Disease
ENDIF

IFSAY Body_Restoration_III
  IFVAR ORG = 20
    ECHO PLAYER Kridash nods to you and chants a spell.
    ECHO OTHERS Kridash nods to %N and chants a spell.
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
    ECHO PLAYER Kridash gestures towards you.
    ECHO OTHERS Kridash gestures towards %N.
    SPELL 318
  ENDIF
ENDIF

IFSAY Cure_Poison
  IFVAR ORG = 20
    ECHO PLAYER Kridash nods to you and chants a spell.
    ECHO OTHERS Kridash nods to %N and chants a spell.
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
    ECHO PLAYER Kridash gestures towards you.
    ECHO OTHERS Kridash gestures towards %N.
    SPELL 303
  ENDIF
ENDIF
NUMBER 1503
NAME Thunderchild, Quarterdeck
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
You find yourself standing on the quarterdeck of the Thunderchild.
Its fire retardant decks show ample signs of use and wear, and thin
metal sheathing covers the outer hulls, as well as reinforcing the main
and foremasts. To the north, an inclined ramp leads to the forecastle,
while a short ladder to the south provides access to the poop deck. An
opening leads down into the cargo holds and quarters. 
*DESCRIPTION_END
