NUMBER 1510
NAME Thunderchild, Forecastle
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
Standing on the forecastle deck, you have an unobstructed view of your
surroundings as well as what is directly ahead. The steel-sheathed
foremast rises from the center of the deck, and overhead, the sails
billow and snap even in the slightest breeze. Extending boldly from the
prow is the familiar carved figure of the Ancestor, Folknar. An inclined
ramp leads back down to the quarterdeck.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 619 VAL2=1503
ITEM 1 639 ADJ1=46 ADJ2=355
EXTEND 1 of the drakin Ancestor, Folknar
IFPREVERB GET 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You examine the figure carefully and realize that it's carved from the prow of the ship. There's no way you can take it.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB STEAL 1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You examine the figure carefully and realize that it's carved from the prow of the ship. There's no way you can take it.
ENDIF
IFPREVERB RECALL 1
  IFVAR RAC = 6
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER Your mind is full of tales of Folknar, the most worshipped of all drakin Ancestors. Sower of the seeds of war and patron of the glory of battle, his figure is one familiar to all drakin.
  ELSE
    IFVAR SKILL32 > 5
      ECHO PLAYER You recognize the figure as that of Folknar, the most worshipped of the drakin Ancestors. He is the embodiment of the spirit of battle and war that characterizes the race.
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CONCENTRATE 1
  IFVAR RAC = 6
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER As you concentrate on the figure of Folknar, your mind fills with scenes of battle and glory. You feel refreshed and invigorated.
    SPELL 335
    SPELL 317
  ENDIF
ENDIF
