NUMBER 1514
NAME Thunderchild, War Room
INDOOR_FLOOR
ASTRAL
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Carefully drawn maps and charts line every wall, most with markings and
pins representing targets and trade routes. Comfortable chairs are set
around an enormous wood table, and in one corner, in a wooden tub, is a
tarokka bush, uprooted from the courtyard of the Castle and carefully
tended. In the center of the table is the crystal ball that once took
pride of place in the Gold Arch Room. A door leads out into the cargo hold.
*DESCRIPTION_END
